round UnsupportedFeature exceptions. If resources are absent, getResourceAsStream returns null, which has implications for testing. I’m considering calling SWT.isLoadable, but I need to ensure that my tests expect the correct behaviors, as a null class resource could lead to a NullPointerException. I see the challenges with existing tests maybe not covering this. So, can I rely on generated metadata for resource inclusion during compilation? There’s a lot to unpack here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_OULqQpmVkdkj79pTQG8q3mEE|fc_07fe491e0040e871016a1ea13f656081938491ed955f8efb26", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata -path '*org.eclipse.swt.win32.win32.x86_64*' -type f -maxdepth 8 | sort | head -20 && find tests/src/org.eclipse.platform/org.eclipse.swt.win32.win32.x86_64/3.133.0/src/test/resources -type f 2>/dev/null | sort"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1153, "output": 516, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21637, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780392244850, "responseId": "resp_07fe491e0040e871016a1ea1358e8c8193bd0cbf952bd95ce1"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_OULqQpmVkdkj79pTQG8q3mEE|fc_07fe491e0040e871016a1ea13f656081938491ed955f8efb26", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "metadata/org.eclipse.platform/org.eclipse.swt.win32.win32.x86_64/3.133.0/reachability-metadata.json\nmetadata/org.eclipse.platform/org.eclipse.swt.win32.win32.x86_64/index.json\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780392255860}]}
